#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:33
#: 8857864fda88403e919e39b798d9c7a3
msgid "Contribution Procedure"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:36
#: 7fcb13a8779f4054a7b318458f245b1d
msgid ""
"Before you start putting serious work into a package, we recommend that "
"you discuss your idea with the Qubes developers and the broader community"
" on the :ref:`qubes-devel mailing list <introduction/support:qubes-"
"devel>`. Once you have a package that’s ready to become part of Qubes OS,"
" please follow this procedure:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:38
#: 005e98f8598c4f5d92fac0c089ea3c92
msgid ""
"Ensure that your package satisfies the `Inclusion Criteria <#inclusion-"
"criteria>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:40
#: ba868ee5abb843049da1babb5ce6dece
msgid ""
"If your code isn’t already on GitHub, create a GitHub repo that contains "
"your code. You can have a look to an example package called `qubes-"
"skeleton <https://github.com/QubesOS-contrib/qubes-skeleton>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:42
#: 74f59c87281e4cd5ac7fd5b7d6a9df96
msgid ""
"If you haven’t already, :doc:`sign your code </developer/code/code-"
"signing>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:44
#: b8de58b84c2943a3b4291b47954fedd3
msgid ""
"Create an issue in `qubes-issues <https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-"
"issues/issues/>`__ with the title ``[Contribution] your-package-name``. "
"Include a link to your repo, a brief description of your package, and a "
"brief explanation of why you think it should be included in Qubes. Please"
" note that the Qubes core developers are very busy. If they are under "
"heavy load when you submit your contribution, it may be a very long time "
"before they have time to review your package. If this happens, please do "
"not be discouraged. If you think they may have forgotten about your "
"pending contribution, you may “bump” your request by commenting on your "
"issue, but please do this *very* sparingly (i.e., no more than once a "
"month). We appreciate your understanding!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:46
#: 6a6f6e6ea9b34090b1f1ee864ce78675
msgid ""
"You may be asked followup questions. If we decide to accept your "
"contribution, you will be invited to join the `QubesOS-contrib "
"<https://github.com/QubesOS-contrib>`__ organization on GitHub as public "
"recognition of your contribution (but without push access; see `Review "
"Procedure <#review-procedure>`__), and `QubesOS-contrib "
"<https://github.com/QubesOS-contrib>`__ will fork your repo. If we decide"
" not to accept your contribution, we will state the reason and close the "
"issue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:51
#: cae56b60b02b4c249b877cf5ee9ee89b
msgid "Update Procedure"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:54
#: acdc3c90261748bd984c4efa1f434b7e
msgid ""
"*Anyone* can provide an update (patch) to a contributed package, not just"
" the person who contributed that package! The update procedure is the "
"same for everyone, including the original package contributor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:56
#: 2edebd708bbd46cea92dbf70c6e16482
msgid ""
"If you would like to update an already-contributed package (specifically,"
" a fork owned by `QubesOS-contrib <https://github.com/QubesOS-"
"contrib>`__), please submit a :doc:`signed </developer/code/code-"
"signing>`, fast-forwardable pull request to that repo with your changes. "
"Please note that your pull request **must** be both :doc:`signed "
"</developer/code/code-signing>` and fast-forwardable, or else it will be "
"closed without further review. One or more reviewers may post comments on"
" your pull request. Please be prepared to read and respond to these "
"comments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:59
#: bb61553b31d241428618fd5cc0581ef3
msgid "Review Procedure"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:62
#: bc8e21838c8b4fb793214c8e479a81d5
msgid ""
"This review procedure covers both original package contributions (see "
"`Contribution Procedure <#contribution-procedure>`__) and all subsequent "
"updates to those packages, including updates from the original package "
"contributor (see `Update Procedure <#update-procedure>`__). All changes "
"will be reviewed by a Qubes Core Reviewer (QCR) and the `Package "
"Maintainer <#package-maintainers>`__ (PM). In all cases, the QCR will be "
"a core Qubes developer. In some cases, the QCR and the PM will be the "
"same person. For example, if someone contributes a package, then "
"disappears, and no suitable replacement has been found, then it is likely"
" that a core Qubes developer will play both the QCR and PM roles for that"
" package, at least until another suitable candidate volunteers to become "
"the PM for that package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:64
#: eff7a21fa65042e08c2e5e73a6cfded3
msgid "The review procedure is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:66
#: a89fd4a8dc1e471b9c98f2bad200485b
msgid "Someone, S, wishes to make a change to a package, P."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:68
#: 80e1fcca53b649e8bb9df218de838715
msgid ""
"S submits a fast-forwardable pull request against the fork of P’s repo "
"owned by `QubesOS-contrib <https://github.com/QubesOS-contrib>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:70
#: bf97bf81c8624366b7d7055151edf4a7
msgid ""
"The PM reviews the pull request. If the pull request passes the PM’s "
"review, the PM adds a :doc:`signed </developer/code/code-signing>` "
"*comment* on the pull request stating that it has passed review. (In "
"cases in which S = PM, the PM can simply add a :doc:`signed "
"</developer/code/code-signing>` *tag* to the HEAD commit prior to "
"submitting the pull request.) If the pull request does not pass the PM’s "
"review, the PM leaves a comment on the pull request explaining why not."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:72
#: cd23fbb65ea740a196b9380f2ab94156
msgid ""
"The QCR reviews the pull request. If the pull request passes the QCR’s "
"review, the QCR pushes a :doc:`signed </developer/code/code-signing>` tag"
" to the HEAD commit stating that it has passed review and fast-forward "
"merges the pull request. If the pull request does not pass the QCR’s "
"review, the QCR leaves a comment on the pull request explaining why not, "
"and the QCR may decide to close the pull request."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:76
#: ea9193a9585448ecaeed0f9873f88b7e
msgid ""
"In all the cases, the first condition to be validated by the QCR’s review"
" is to ensure that the contribution **will not** hijack any core packages"
" of `QubesOS <https://github.com/QubesOS>`__ and of course, none of the "
"`QubesOS-contrib <https://github.com/QubesOS-contrib>`__ packages too. "
"More precisely, particular attention to the whole build pipeline will be "
"made with a specific review of:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:78
#: bdb965e2d657464e97670f0403f03881
msgid "Package dependencies,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:80
#: bfefd7da9924417c96f76cabb5bf8e39
msgid "Build scripts (including downloaded ones),"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:82
#: babb03d8e78e4061a2693e7629439588
msgid "All downloaded components should be verified against static hash,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:84
#: 3df2c483a7754fa382800e849150b3b0
msgid ""
"RPM/DEB installation scripts (e.g. looking at constraints who would "
"hijack other packages),"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:86
#: afdd3be74f7f4ed9acdb462ed41a4212
msgid "Makefiles,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:88
#: 6b5e4f0be95d4ff4ad77f61a0fdfe2e7
msgid "Package build `reproducible <https://reproducible-builds.org/>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:92
#: 2589e88b460344409c60690c56a9e5fa
msgid ""
"and any steps which would result in partial/total compromise of "
"legitimate components. For this part, you can have a look to an example "
"package called `qubes-skeleton <https://github.com/QubesOS-contrib/qubes-"
"skeleton>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:95
#: a77442f3794c410ebb5aba4ac29e63cf
msgid "Package Maintainers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:98
#: e31633f6fbef45b5bdfdbb2af9301310
msgid ""
"If you contribute a package, we assume that you will be the maintainer of"
" that package, unless you tell us otherwise. As the maintainer of the "
"package, it is your privilege and responsibility to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:100
#: 7d9c1f3148224086b6638ac002e8082b
msgid "`Review <#review-procedure>`__ each pull request made against the package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:102
#: 1e29537083fc41139e95db0ef1ecd8a6
msgid ""
"Decide when the package has reached a new version, and notify the Qubes "
"core developers when this occurs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/package-contributions.rst:106
#: acfc3636f912447b8e4c2da5c5c34104
msgid ""
"If you do not wish to be the maintainer of your package, please let us "
"know. If you do not act on your maintainer duties for a given package for"
" an extended period of time and after at least one reminder, we will "
"assume that you no longer wish to be the maintainer for that package."
msgstr ""

